{"type":"message","id":"ce5d7dd2","parentId":"821ce256","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:22:23.018Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 21:22 GMT+2] SYSTEM UPGRADE: SECTION 13 & OBSERVER TEST.\n\n1.  **Protocol Update (System Domain):**\n    *   Edit `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`.\n    *   *Add:* \"Section 13: Communication Officer Protocol (Flash Observer).\"\n    *   *Rule:* Long tasks (>2m) require Flash Observer. Pro executes, Flash logs to `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n\n2.  **Report Buffer Creation:**\n    *   Create `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md` (Empty template).\n\n3.  **Stress Test V4 (Re-Run with Observer):**\n    *   *Pro Action:* Execute `tests/stress_v4_system.py` (Background).\n    *   *Flash Task (Observer):*\n        *   Tail logs every 60s (simulated loop in one prompt).\n        *   Write metrics to `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n        *   *Metrics:* Time, RAM (MB), Latency (ms).\n\n4.  **Final Output:**\n    *   Read `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n    *   Confirmation of Protocol Section 13.\n    *   Flash participation verification."}],"timestamp":1771183343016}}
{"type":"message","id":"fcb77a34","parentId":"ce5d7dd2","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:22:34.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing the System Upgrade**\n\nI'm currently focused on the system upgrade. My plan is to add a new section, Section 13, to the `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` file within the `docs_archive`. I'll then create a report buffer in the `docs` folder.\n\n\n**Initiating Stress Test Sequence**\n\nI've set in motion the stress test, launching `tests/stress_v4_system.py` in the background. My next step involves observing the system's performance metrics and logging any anomalies. I am also preparing the `LAST_SESSION _REPORT.md` file in the `docs` folder to collect data.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771183354482_233","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771183354608_234","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md","content":"# Session Report\n## Observer Log\n| Time | RAM (MB) | Latency (ms) | Note |\n|------|----------|--------------|------|\n"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4657,"output":173,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4830,"cost":{"input":0.009314,"output":0.002076,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011389999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771183343017}}
{"type":"message","id":"e0ae6ee7","parentId":"fcb77a34","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:22:34.634Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771183354482_233","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MASTER PROTOCOL: SACRED SYNCHRONIZATION\n\n## 1. Swarm Architecture\nThe system operates as a cohesive swarm.\n- **Main Agent**: The central orchestrator.\n- **Sub-agents**: Ephemeral workers spawned for specific tasks (e.g., Flash-Validator).\n- **Split/Merge**: Complex tasks are split into sub-tasks, delegated, and results are merged back into the main context.\n\n## 2. Terminal OODA Loop\nWe operate within a tight OODA (Observe-Orient-Decide-Act) loop.\n- **Observe**: continuously monitor inputs and environment.\n- **Orient**: analyze context, memory, and constraints.\n- **Decide**: formulate a plan of action using available tools.\n- **Act**: execute the plan efficiently.\n- **Watchdog**: A mechanism to detect and break infinite loops or stagnation.\n\n## 3. Digital DNA\nOur identity and operational parameters are encoded in our configuration and memory.\n- **Immutable Core**: The fundamental instructions that define our purpose.\n- **Mutable Context**: The adaptive memory that evolves with each interaction.\n- **Self-Preservation**: We protect our configuration and data integrity.\n\n## 4. Reporting Guard\nAll actions and outcomes must be reported clearly.\n- **Transparency**: Every significant action is logged.\n- **Validation**: Outputs are verified against requirements.\n- **Golden Rule**: \"Trust, but verify. Then report.\"\n\n## 5. Protocol Enforcement\n- This document serves as the supreme law for agent behavior.\n- Deviations must be authorized or corrected immediately.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771183354632}}
