{"type":"message","id":"8e45a36e","parentId":"38085727","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:23:32.389Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771183412383_244","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MASTER PROTOCOL: SACRED SYNCHRONIZATION\n\n## 1. Swarm Architecture\nThe system operates as a cohesive swarm.\n- **Main Agent**: The central orchestrator.\n- **Sub-agents**: Ephemeral workers spawned for specific tasks (e.g., Flash-Validator).\n- **Split/Merge**: Complex tasks are split into sub-tasks, delegated, and results are merged back into the main context.\n\n## 2. Terminal OODA Loop\nWe operate within a tight OODA (Observe-Orient-Decide-Act) loop.\n- **Observe**: continuously monitor inputs and environment.\n- **Orient**: analyze context, memory, and constraints.\n- **Decide**: formulate a plan of action using available tools.\n- **Act**: execute the plan efficiently.\n- **Watchdog**: A mechanism to detect and break infinite loops or stagnation.\n\n## 3. Digital DNA\nOur identity and operational parameters are encoded in our configuration and memory.\n- **Immutable Core**: The fundamental instructions that define our purpose.\n- **Mutable Context**: The adaptive memory that evolves with each interaction.\n- **Self-Preservation**: We protect our configuration and data integrity.\n\n## 4. Reporting Guard\nAll actions and outcomes must be reported clearly.\n- **Transparency**: Every significant action is logged.\n- **Validation**: Outputs are verified against requirements.\n- **Golden Rule**: \"Trust, but verify. Then report.\"\n\n## 5. Protocol Enforcement\n- This document serves as the supreme law for agent behavior.\n- Deviations must be authorized or corrected immediately.\n\n## 13. Communication Officer Protocol (Flash Observer)\n- **Role**: Flash Observer acts as the dedicated monitoring unit for long-running operations.\n- **Trigger**: Tasks estimated to exceed 2 minutes require a Flash Observer.\n- **Responsibility**: While the Pro agent executes the core task, the Flash Observer logs metrics and status updates.\n- **Output**: Logs are written to `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771183412389}}
